HEADWORD: Weber
<hw>We"ber</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From the name of
Professor <ets>Weber</ets>, a German electrician.]</ety>
<fld>(Elec.)</fld> <def>The standard unit of electrical quantity, and
also of current. See <er>Coulomb</er>, and <er>Ampere</er>.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

